  "prompt": "When I eat sushi, what is the eel sauce made of?",
  "response": "Eel sauce, also known as **unagi sauce** or **kabayaki sauce**, is a savory, slightly sweet glaze commonly served with sushi, particularly with eel (unagi) dishes. It is made from a combination of a few key ingredients:\n\n1. **Soy Sauce**: Provides the base flavor and saltiness.  \n2. **Mirin**: A sweet rice wine that adds sweetness and depth.  \n3. **Sugar**: Enhances the sweetness and creates a glossy, syrupy consistency.  \n\nThe sauce is typically simmered together to thicken and concentrate the flavors. Some variations may include ingredients like sake, dashi, or honey for added complexity. The result is a rich, umami-packed sauce that complements the flavor of grilled eel and other sushi dishes.",
